<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24837" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Hypoponera Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hypoponera</taxonomicName>
was split off by Santschi (1938) as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24845" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera Latreille" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ponera</taxonomicName>
and was subsequently given full generic status by Taylor (1967). It is characterised by the one segmented maxillary palp and absence of ventral ornamentation on the petiole. The genus includes a large number of small hypogoeic species occurring throughout the tropics with four species in South Europe of which only one occurs north of latitude 47°.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
